  <li><a href="#nav" title="Navigation template">Navigation Template</a></li>
</ul>

<h3><a name="overview"></a>Overview</h3>
<p>All templates reside in the /sitespecific/templates directory. The sections below provide more
   detail as to the purpose, usage, and data available in each type of template.</p>
<p class="back-to-top"><a href="#top" title="Back to top">Back to top</a></p>

<h3><a name="primary"></a>Primary Template</h3>
<h4>Purpose</h4>
<p>The primary template defines the overall structure for a page.
   WalkerCMS places the output from this template directly into the &lt;body&gt; tag.</p>
<h4>Usage</h4>
<p>The primary template has a filename of &quot;inner_template.php&quot; and is required to be present
   for a website using WalkerCMS.</p>
<p>It is possible to use any valid PHP in the template as long as it is surrounded by any of the
   possible PHP tags. For example, the copyright year in the footer of this page is generated by the
   following:<code>&lt;?= date('Y') ?&gt;</code></p>
<h4>Available Variables</h4>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Variable</th>
      <th>Data type</th>
      <th>Description</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">content_page_id</td>
      <td class="data-type">string</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>
          If a page is configured as a parent that contains sub-navigation but it has no content defined,
          then WalkerCMS will populate the page with the content of the first child. This variable
          contains the ID of the page that supplied the content.</p>
        <p>For example, the <span class="page-id">docs</span> page has no content but has two children
          pages, <span class="page-id">overview</span> and <span class="page-id">api</span>. When a user
          requests the <span class="page-id">docs</span> page, the <span class="page-id">overview</span>
          content will be displayed and the <span class="variable-name">content_page_id</span> variable
          will be set to <span class="page-id">overview</span>).
        </p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
          <li><a href="content" title="Creating Content">Creating Content</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">has_contact_form</td>
      <td class="data-type">boolean</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>
          Indicates whether a contact form is expected on the current page or not. This depends
          on whether the currently requested page matches the value of the
          <span class="setting-name">contact_page</span> configuration setting.
        </p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
          <li><a href="content" title="Creating Content">Creating Content</a></li>
          <li><a href="extrafeatures" title="Extra Features">Extra Features</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">has_page_specific_footer</td>
      <td class="data-type">boolean</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Indicates whether the requested page has a custom footer defined.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="content" title="Creating Content">Creating Content</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">has_page_specific_header</td>
      <td class="data-type">boolean</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Indicates whether the requested page has a custom header defined.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="content" title="Creating Content">Creating Content</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">has_page_specific_html_header</td>
      <td class="data-type">boolean</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Indicates whether the requested page has a custom inclusion for the &lt;head&gt; section.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="content" title="Creating Content">Creating Content</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">has_page_specific_javascript</td>
      <td class="data-type">boolean</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Indicates whether the requested page has a custom defined javascript file.
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="content" title="Creating Content">Creating Content</a></li>
        </ul> 
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">has_page_specific_stylesheet</td>
      <td class="data-type">boolean</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Indicates whether the requested page has a custom-defined stylesheet.
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="content" title="Creating Content">Creating Content</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">has_secondary_content</td>
      <td class="data-type">boolean</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Indicates whether the requested page has secondary content.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="content" title="Creating Content">Creating Content</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">has_sub_nav</td>
      <td class="data-type">boolean</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Indicates whether the page contains sub navigation or not. This depends on whether the page
           is configured to have children and whether the page should show the sub-navigation on it.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
          <li><a href="content" title="Creating Content">Creating Content</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">minimum_ie_version</td>
      <td class="data-type">string</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Indicates which version of Internet Explorer is your minimum for support. This works
           in conjunction with the <span class="variable-name">show_ie_warning</span> variable below.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
          <li><a href="extrafeatures" title="Extra Features">Extra Features</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">organization_full_title</td>
      <td class="data-type">string</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Contains the configured full name of the organization for which you are creating a
           website. Generally, this will be the full legal corporation name and comes directly
           from the site configuration.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">organization_name</td>
      <td class="data-type">string</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Contains the familiar name of the organization for which you are creating a website.
           This value comes directly from the site configuration.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">organization_slogan</td>
      <td class="data-type">string</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Contains the slogan for the organization for which you are building a website. This
           value comes directly from the site configuration.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">page_id</td>
      <td class="data-type">string</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Contains the requested validated page ID.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="overview" title="WalkerCMS Overview">Overview</a></li>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">page_title</td>
      <td class="data-type">string</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Contains the configured page title.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">show_ie_warning</td>
      <td class="data-type">boolean</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Indicates whether to show a warning to users that have a version Internet Explorer less
           than or equal to the <span class="variable-name">minimum_ie_version</span> supported by
           this website.
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
          <li><a href="extrafeatures" title="Extra Features">Extra Features</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">site</td>
      <td class="data-type">string</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Contains the configured website ID.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">site_description</td>
      <td class="data-type">string</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Contains the description of the website. Generally used in the &lt;head&gt; section
           for the meta description. This value comes directly from the site configuration.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="variable-name">site_keywords</td>
      <td class="data-type">string</td>
      <td class="variable-desc">
        <p>Contains the keywords for the website. Generally used in the &lt;head&gt; section
           for the meta keywords. This value comes directly from the site configuration.</p>
        <p>See also:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="config" title="Configuring WalkerCMS">Configuration</a></li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
